  "prompt": "How can I change my IP address?",
  "response": "There are several ways to change your IP address:\n\n1. Use a VPN (Virtual Private Network)\n- Most reliable and secure method\n- Masks your real IP with a different one\n- Many free and paid options available\n\n2. Use a proxy server\n- Routes internet traffic through a different IP\n- Less secure than a VPN\n\n3. Restart your router\n- Can sometimes assign a new IP from your ISP\n- Works best with dynamic IP addresses\n\n4. Connect to a different network\n- Use mobile data instead of WiFi\n- Switch between WiFi networks\n\n5. Use Tor browser\n- Routes traffic through multiple servers\n- Provides anonymity\n\n6. Contact your Internet Service Provider\n- Request a new IP address\n- May require specific procedures\n\n7. Use mobile hotspot\n- Creates a different network connection\n\nEach method has pros and cons, so choose based on your specific needs and privacy requirements.",
